statement.p:
A list of boundary tangent vectors
\mathbf v_1,\ldots,\mathbf v_{k-1}
is positively oriented on \partial M if the list
\boxed{\nu_{\text{out}},\mathbf v_1,\ldots,\mathbf v_{k-1}}
is positively oriented in M.

subsection.md:
\begin{array}{c|c|c}
M \amp \nu_{\text{out}} \amp \text{Resulting boundary orientation} \\ \hline
[a,b] \amp
\begin{array}{c}
- \text{ direction at }a\\
+ \text{ direction at }b
\end{array}
\amp
\partial[a,b]=\{b\}-\{a\}
\\[5mm]
\text{plane region with }dx\wedge dy \amp
\text{outward direction in the plane} \amp
\text{region stays on the left}
\\[2mm]
\text{surface with normal }\mathbf n \amp
\text{outward direction along the surface} \amp
\text{right-hand rule around the boundary}
\\[2mm]
\text{solid with }dx\wedge dy\wedge dz \amp
\text{outward normal in space} \amp
\text{outward-oriented boundary surface}
\end{array}
